2. That they teach Man the Knowledge of him∣self;
they fully discover him to himself, and that
in a very particular and inimitable Manner.

SP.P:
I am glad to hear my Father say so;
for it has much puzzled my Thoughts sometimes,
seeing the bold Flourishes they make upon it.

I am astonish'd at the Evidence of it;
I never enter'd into that Part of it; I think no∣thing
is clearer in the World.

The Article of Christ's Miracles is very con∣vincing;
I think he might well say, Believe me for
the Works sake.

